{
    "identity": "nprot-467",
    "title": "Heart ink injection",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Introduction",
            "content": "With this technique it is possible to label the blood vessel _in vivo_ in order to analyze in whole mount the quantity and quality of blood vessel."
        },
        {
            "header": "Reagents",
            "content": "1.0 ml syringe\r\n\n\nChina Black Ink  \r\n\n\nStadard anesthetic \\(Ketamine and Xylazine)"
        },
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "1. Anesthetize the mouse\r\n  2. Using a 1 ml syringe withdraw 0,5 ml of mouse blood from the heart ventricle \r\n  3. Inject 1 ml of China Ink and wait for 30 sec \\(until the eyes, mouth and legs became black)\r\n  4. Quickly dissect and fix in 4% PFA over night at 4\u00b0C\r\n  5. Treat the sample with a solution of 0,5% KOH for one day \r\n  6. Treat the sample with a solution of 0,5% KOH/Glycarol 2:1 one day\r\n  7. Treat the sample with a solution of 0,5% KOH/Glycerol 1:1 for one day\r\n  8. Treat the sample with 100% Glycerol for one day \\(in order to visualize clearly all the inner blood vessels)"
        },
        {
            "header": "Timing",
            "content": "4 days"
        },
        {
            "header": "Critical Steps",
            "content": "Injection in the heart after blood withdrawal"
        },
        {
            "header": "Anticipated Results",
            "content": "eyes, mouth and legs black stained"
        }
    ],
